In its complete form, background-averaged epistasis considers averages over all possible genotypes for the remaining positions in the ensemble. For example, if n = 3, the epistasis between two positions 1 and 2 is computed as an average over both states of the third position (ε*11, with the averaging denoted by a subscript “*”) (see Fig 1C):




ε*11=12{[(y111−y110)−(y101−y100)]+[(y011−y010)−(y001−y000)]}


